---
description: Documentation and markdown update rules
globs: "**/*.md,docs/**/*"
---

- Keep documentation aligned with the current code, commands, and file paths. Remove stale examples instead of leaving conflicting notes.
- Prefer short sections, direct wording, and task-oriented examples over long narrative explanations.
- When documenting workflows, include prerequisites, command examples, and expected outcomes.
- If a behavior changed in code, update the nearest README, reference, or operational doc in the same change.
- Follow the project documentation conventions and terminology from `CLAUDE.md`.

@CLAUDE.md
